OL,3,CVeteran thrown out of Navy for being
OL,4,Cgay 'elated' as compensation announced
OL,6,FA man from Plymouth who arrested,
OL,7,Fdetained and thrown out of the Royal
OL,8,FNavy for being gay has welcomed a
OL,9,Fgovernment compensation scheme -
OL,10,Fsaying it's been a long time coming.
OL,12,FMartyn Hammond, 60, was among many
OL,13,Fservice personnel who faced
OL,14,Fdiscrimination as a result of the ban
OL,15,Fon homosexuality in place between 1967
OL,16,Fand 2000.
OL,18,FThe Ministry of Defence has now
OL,19,Fconfirmed veterans who were dismissed
OL,20,Fwill be eligible to receive up to
OL,21,F#70,000 in compensation.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
